e of the journal Science, spent 18 years determining thethree-dimensional arrangement of RuBisCO, a protein that sustainslife by making plants grow.   Such knowledge eventually may help researchers design proteinsto kill cancers, treat diabetes, destroy blood clots and even makebetter laundry detergents.</TEXT><DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Greece assumes the presidency of theEuropean Economic Community midway into a year that has producedsome of the biggest successes in the trade bloc's 31-year historybut still faces friction with the United States over farm trade.   The socialist government of Prime Minister Andreas Papandreou,which often is out of step with the priorities of its 11 EECpartners, takes over the rotating presidency from West Germanytoday. He is likely to emphasize improving the economic prospectsof Europe's poorer and less industrialized regions.</TEXT><BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE><TEXT>   Stock prices rose broadly Thursday, with the Dow Jones averageof 30 industrials closing up 19.73 points at 2,141.71.   Bond prices moved higher. The Treasury's long bond was up about$6 per $1,000 in face amount; its yield fell to 8.85 percent from8.92 percent late Wednesday.   The dollar finished narrowly mixed. Gold prices were mixed.   Crude oil futures prices fell to their lowest level this year inactive trading, while soybean futures shot higher on renewed fearsof drought damage.</TEXT></DOC>